    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_4058360591" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4058360591" />
    <a title="JohnnyBear" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/136436847-johnnybear"><img alt="JohnnyBear" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1623697192p2/136436847.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4058360591?book_show_action=true">Jun 14, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="JohnnyBear" class="user" itemprop="url" name="JohnnyBear" href="/user/show/136436847-johnnybear">JohnnyBear</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/136436847-johnnybear?shelf=contemporary">contemporary</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/136436847-johnnybear?shelf=middle-grade">middle-grade</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4058360591" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17448509697379267937"><b>Strong 8 out of 10</b><br/><br/> Ghost is about a boy named Castle who is considerably faster than most of the kids in his school. He auditions for his local track team and impresses the coach with his speed on the track. He ends up getting picked for the team, and this book explores his life on the team, and how he tries to fit in with everyone despite not being well-off.<br/><br/> <img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1468787024l/28954126.jpg' width='200' height='300' alt='Book Cover' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/> I don&apos;t generally like books about sports, but this was an exception. I really found myself liking this book. I was surprised by how emot</span>
  <span id="freeText17448509697379267937" style="display:none"><b>Strong 8 out of 10</b><br><br> Ghost is about a boy named Castle who is considerably faster than most of the kids in his school. He auditions for his local track team and impresses the coach with his speed on the track. He ends up getting picked for the team, and this book explores his life on the team, and how he tries to fit in with everyone despite not being well-off.<br><br> <img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1468787024l/28954126.jpg" width="200" height="300" alt="Book Cover" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br> I don't generally like books about sports, but this was an exception. I really found myself liking this book. I was surprised by how emotional it was, and how well it dealt with harder topics. Castle is a great character and has a fantastic character arc. I also liked some of his friends, which would be Sunny, Patina, and Lu. <i>Later on, it seems that they have their own books in the "Track" series.</i><br><br> Fantastic book. Even if you're not generally a fan of books about sports, I'd still recommend this book, especially if you're in the middle-grade demographic. I was surprised by how emotionally invested I was in this story.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17448509697379267937" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


